banner.short_description: Aladdin, a kind thief, woos Jasmine, the princess of Agrabah, with the help of Genie. When Jafar, the grand vizier, tries to usurp the king, Jasmine, Aladdin and Genie must stop him from succeeding.
Murad Ali Mohammed and his daughter-in-law try to prove their innocence after their family gets accused of having ties with extremist groups when Mohammed's son joins a terrorist outfit.
A small-town stock trader, Rizwan Ahmed, comes to Mumbai and gets employed by the successful Gujarati trader, Shakun Kothari. Everything seems to be going smooth until Rizwan hits a rough patch.
An ambitious young boy, Dilsher, develops a speech impairment after his father's death. Initially, Dilsher is hesitant to pursue singing but Amira changes his mind and persuades to try it.

banner.movie_name: Without you Bin Laden: Dead or Alive
banner.short_description: Without you Bin Laden: Dead or Alive) is a 2016 Indian comedy film written and directed by Abhishek Sharma. A sequel to the 2010 film Tere Bin Laden, it narrates the story of an aspiring filmmaker who bumps into an Osama bin Laden look alike, and also samples materials from the prequel.
Kabir, a genius yet hostile medical student, falls in love with Preeti from his college. When Preeti's father spots the couple kissing, he opposes their relationship and decides to marry her off.

Bram Stoker's Dracula is a 1992 American Gothic horror film directed and produced by Francis Ford Coppola, based on the 1897 novel Dracula by Bram Stoker.It stars Gary Oldman as Count Dracula, Winona Ryder as Mina Harker, Anthony Hopkins as Professor Abraham Van Helsing, and Keanu Reeves as Jonathan Harker.

Dracula was theatrically released in the United States on November 13, 1992, to positive reviews,[7][8] though Keanu Reeves' performance and English accent received criticism.[9][10][11] The film grossed $215 million against a production budget of $40 million. It was nominated for four Academy Awards and won three for Best Costume Design, Best Sound Editing, and Best Makeup while also being nominated for Best Art Direction

data.tvv_description: Balasaheb Thackeray, a cartoonist with a no-nonsense personality, plays a key role in the birth of the Shiv Sena and goes on to become the most influential political leader in Maharashtra.
